> Because of how well red kidney beans hold their shape during cooking they're perfect
> for simmered dishes like this one. This veggie curry is filled with protein,
> fibre and of course, plenty of flavour.

Add @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) to a #medium pot{} with a
tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pot from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) into small pieces.

Trim half the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and quartered lengthways) (double for 4p),
then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Quarter the @lemon{1/2}.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}. Mash half with a
#fork{}.

Place a #large pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

When hot, add half the chopped onion and fry for ~{4-5%mins}.

Add the @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and fry for ~{1%min}.

Pour in the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack} and beans (both mashed
and whole).

Cover and simmer for ~{10-12%mins}. Add the @garam masala{1%sachet} when the
curry has ~{2%mins} left to simmer.

== Cucumber and Coriander Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{} mix the chopped cucumber, remaining chopped onion and
half the coriander.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @lemon juice{to taste}.

== Curry Finish ==

Stir half the @creme fraiche{125%g} into the curry and allow to warm through.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to loosen the curry if required.

== To Serve ==

Divide the curry between #bowls{} with spoonfuls of fluffy rice.

Squeeze over remaining lemon juice to taste.

Top with remaining coriander and creme fraiche.

Serve with cucumber salad alongside.